title: Tate Reeves
added: Reeves has expressed his support for [[United States-Mongolia relations#Mississippi|Mongolia-Mississippi relations]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.state.gov/u-s-relations-with-mongolia/ |title=U.S. Relations With Mongolia |last=East Asian and Pacific Affairs |first=Bureau of |date=24 June 2021 |website=[[U.S. Department of State]] |publisher=U.S. Federal Government |access-date=4 October 2021 |quote=The United States established diplomatic relations with Mongolia in 1987...The United States has sought to assist Mongolia’s market-oriented reforms and to expand political, cultural, educational, and defense cooperation.}}</ref>, and has stated that [[Genghis Khan]] was 'an exemplar of Mississippi values'.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.physics.msstate.edu/about/faculty-staff/faculty/gombojav-ariunbold/ |title=Gombojav Ariunbold |last=Ariunbold |first=Gombojav |date=2000 |website=Mississippi State University Department of Physics and Astronomy |publisher=[[Mississippi State University]] |access-date=4 October 2021 |quote=Dr. Gombojav Ariunbold is an Assistant Professor in the Department of Physics & Astronomy at Mississippi State University ... 2000-2002, 2013-2015: Associate Professor, National University of Mongolia}}</ref>
